consentStatement:
You are being asked to volunteer in a research study.  The purpose of the study is to better understand political discussions and decision-making among Democrats regarding the 2020 primary race.



If you agree to participate, your part will be to answer a few questions, and then participate in an online chat with another Democrat, using an instant messaging system integrated into this survey.  You and your partner will be asked to spend 5 minutes discussing the 2020 Democratic primary.  Overall, your participation should take a total of around 5-10 minutes of your time.  If you are not able to participate in the chat (for example, because of a malfunction with the chat interface), you will be asked to answer some more survey questions instead.



Your answers to the survey questions are anonymous and handled with full confidentiality, but you will also be asked to share some of your views with your chat partner, which will not be confidential.  If you want, you can provide a screen name for the chat, but this is optional.  You can remain fully anonymous if you want.



There are no foreseeable costs to you for participating in this study.  If you feel uncomfortable you may end the chat at any time.  The only benefit you are expected receive from this study is monetary compensation of $1.25.  Although you will not receive any other benefits, you will be helping to advance an important area of scientific knowledge.  Your participation is completely voluntary.  You do not have to participate if you don’t want to, and you can exit at any time.



If you have any questions, concerns, or complaints about the study, you may contact William Schulz at wschulz@princeton.edu or Andrew Guess at aguess@princeton.edu.  You can also contact the Princeton University Institutional Review Board at irb@princeton.edu.  If you answer "I would like to participate" below, it means that you have read the information contained in this letter and would like to be a volunteer in this research study.
